The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Nato attack 

 Kabul, April 8 (Reuters): Six Nato soldiers were killed in southern Afghanistan today when their vehicle was hit by a roadside bomb, a coalition spokesman said. At least one soldier was injured in the single worst incident for the Nato forces in several months. 

 Earlier today, one Nato soldier was killed and another injured by a similar bomb in another part of south Afghanistan, a spokeswoman said. 

 Bangla flu 

 Dhaka (Reuters): Bangladesh has culled 3,000 chickens after an outbreak of bird flu was confirmed at a new farm near Dhaka, officials said on Sunday. 




